40
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:47,080
[song playing]

41
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,680
Nandini!

42
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:02,120
Nandini!

43
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,320
Nandini!

44
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,480
Yes, tell me, Mehul.

45
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:09,320
Come quickly! Emergency!

46
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:12,840
- Nandini!
- I am coming.

47
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,840
You make them practice. I am coming.

48
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,360
Nandini, hurry up.

49
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:24,560
Nandini!

50
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:28,560
[intense music]

51
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:33,400
What happened, Mehul?

52
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:35,200
Nandini! The farm
is being auctioned off.

53
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:37,920
Uncle is in the bank. Think of
something quickly. What do we do?

54
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,080
Let's go home.

55
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:41,080
The auction is being
held in the bank.

56
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,720
Let's go home.

57
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,120
Yes, let's go.

58
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,600
- What?
- Helmet.

59
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:50,760
I have worn it. Let's go.

60
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,200
Hey!

61
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,920
[intense music]

62
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:06,160
Rs. 2,02,500.
Tell me if you want to give it.

63
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,360
Okay, let's go. Is there anyone?

64
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,360
Three lakh rupees!

65
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:11,720
Three lakh rupees!
Very good. Anyone else?

66
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:14,680
- Three lakh, fifty thousand rupees!
- Three lakh, fifty thousand rupees!

67
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,080
Four lakh, fifty thousand rupees!

68
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:17,880
Four lakh, fifty thousand rupees!
Very good.

69
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:20,400
It was the land of our ancestors.

70
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:24,800
I couldn't save it.

71
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:32,120
Aunt, I am sorry. Did you get hurt?

72
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:36,720
Get down.

73
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,840
The hay has also finished.

74
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:44,360
There is no one to look
after the house except me.

75
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:47,320
No one is concerned
about anything except me.

76
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,880
What is going on?

77
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:53,360
Surbhi, you have been
ringing the bell since morning.

78
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:56,000
There is no one in
this house except me.

79
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:58,080
Did someone give you grass?

80
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:01,040
No one does anything.

81
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,640
No one helps me.

82
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:06,120
No one does anything
in this house except Mani.

83
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:08,960
- I do all the work.
- Aunt!

84
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:11,360
What is this?
Where have you been since morning?

85
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,040
Forget all that. Put this aside.

86
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:15,840
One minute. Take this off.

87
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:18,200
[chuckles]

88
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:20,960
You have such a photogenic face.

89
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:24,200
Come here. I will show you
how beautiful you are.

90
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,320
Don't flatter me.

91
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:27,800
I am not flattering you.
I am telling the truth.

92
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,880
Wait a minute. Here.

93
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,920
Stand like this. Yes.

94
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:36,000
Here... Yes!

95
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,920
- Hey!
- Aunt!

96
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:40,120
Yes!

97
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:41,320
Aunt, do you know?

98
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:44,960
In Upleta, they put up big posters
of the pictures I click.

99
00:06:58,320 --> 00:07:00,240
[sad music]

100
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,200
'Uncle.'

101
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,520
'All these ornaments...'

102
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,240
'Are they all ours?'

103
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:14,360
'Nandu, these are the ornaments'

104
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:17,400
'that my mother gave your mother.'

105
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:20,120
'And these are the ornaments
of my mother that I got.'

106
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,480
'I saved all these
for your wedding.'

107
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,080
'Why do we need so many ornaments?'

108
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:27,400
'What else does a bride
need except a nuptial chain?'

109
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,800
'Nandu, this is your dowry.'

110
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,800
[sad music]

111
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:47,760
[suspenseful music]

112
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,480
[suspenseful music]

113
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:54,360
Very good, Aunt. Very good.

114
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:56,400
Yes.

115
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:58,800
Okay.

116
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,480
Yes.

117
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,920
Come on.
This is the last auction of the day.

118
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:06,280
Ishwar Tambariya's farm.

119
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,640
Six acres of land.
There is a well on the farm.

120
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,520
There is a fence as well.

121
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,920
And there is an electric pump too.

122
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:16,040
And the base price for this
is nine lakh rupees.

123
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:22,880
[intense music]

124
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:35,560
[intense music]

125
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,240
Thank you, Uncle.

126
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:42,040
Nine lakh rupees.
Tell me. Is there anyone?

127
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:43,680
Nine lakh and twenty-five
thousand rupees.

128
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,080
Nine lakh and twenty-five
thousand rupees.

129
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,080
Nine lakh and fifty thousand rupees.

130
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:47,360
Nine lakh and fifty thousand rupees.
One.

131
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,520
[intense music]

132
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,520
- Nine lakh and fifty thousand
rupees. Two. - Ten lakh rupees!

133
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,520
Ten lakh rupees.

134
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,600
Ten lakh rupees. One.

135
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:01,080
- Ten lakh rupees! Two. Ten lakh...
- Hold on!

136
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,680
[intense music]

137
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,280
Sorry

138
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:19,000
to stop your auction like this.

139
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:29,400
Sir. Here's the loan amount of ten
lakh rupees taken by Uncle Ishwar

140
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,880
and the interest in it.

141
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,960
You can take it.

142
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:37,400
It's twelve lakh fifty
thousand rupees.

143
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:40,280
Please don't auction
my uncle's farm.

144
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,800
Okay. You...

145
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:48,160
You wait for a while.
I will tell you.

146
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,840
Okay.

147
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:53,320
[intense music]

148
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:02,440
Mr Ishwar owes eleven lakh and
seventy-five thousand to the bank.

149
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:04,800
You have paid for it.

150
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:06,960
So the auction can stop.

151
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,480
[intense music]

152
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,720
Sir, give me the file.

153
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:16,320
Come in, Mr Ishwar.

154
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:21,240
Mr Ishwar, you are so lucky.

155
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:25,160
Now, there is no interest or loan.

156
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:28,080
Now your farm will be with you.

157
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:29,720
Take this.

158
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:31,800
Sign on this.

159
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,640
Get it signed by the registrar too.

160
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:39,080
And take the receipt
of your money from outside.

161
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:40,640
Leave the money here.

162
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:42,720
The rest of the money
will be returned to you.

163
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,560
Uncle, I have seen
all these papers.

164
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:51,520
I will get the
registrar's sign on this.

165
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:54,000
- Mehul, you sit with Uncle
and make him drink tea. - Yes.

166
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,760
I'll be back. Come on, Mitesh.

167
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,680
It's hot. We'll drink
buttermilk instead of tea.

168
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:03,000
- Ms Nandini.
- Yes.

169
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:06,840
I believe that

170
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:10,400
you have saved the land
of the farm with great difficulty.

171
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:14,160
Sorry. I am Parag Kanhabar.

172
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:17,040
I work for the politician and MLA

173
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,920
Mr Arjan Khimji here.

174
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:22,760
As a well-wisher,
I have an offer for you.

175
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:27,160
If we offer you 20 lakh rupees
in return for your land

176
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:30,160
can you tell your uncle

177
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:32,640
to transfer your land to us?

178
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:34,360
Thank you for your offer.

179
00:11:34,560 --> 00:11:36,240
But we don't want
to sell this farm.

180
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,920
Come on, Mitesh.

181
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:41,200
[intense music]

182
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,960
Yes, sir.

183
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:58,000
Sir,

184
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:01,640
the man's niece came

185
00:12:01,880 --> 00:12:03,000
and stopped the auction.

186
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:06,120
What did you do, Nandu?
Have you gone mad?

187
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,880
You sold the ornaments.

188
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:10,000
Do you know what your aunt
will do if she finds out?

189
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,440
She will create havoc.

190
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:13,960
Uncle, you don't have to
tell Aunt anything right now.

191
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:16,320
It's wrong to hide the truth.

192
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:19,160
You hid it from us.
And from Aunt Mani.

193
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,720
Did you tell anyone

194
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,920
that you have mortgaged the farm?

195
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,800
Don't ask me questions.

196
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:26,680
The ornaments were
for your wedding.

197
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,440
You sold them for my land.

198
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:35,160
Uncle, the gold will
remain in the safe.

199
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:38,480
The gold will grow on the farm.

200
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:43,320
But you can't risk your land

201
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:46,200
for the ornaments.

202
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,520
Uncle, your daughter will leave

203
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:51,240
what will be left with you,
if you lose the farm as well?

204
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:58,080
It's good that Mitesh
told me everything.

205
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:03,040
You come in the rickshaw with Mehul.
Uncle, come with me.

206
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,920
[happy music]

207
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:23,640
[happy music]

208
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,440
Uncle!

209
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:35,840
Uncle,

210
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:39,240
don't tell Aunt about the ornaments.

211
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,920
She will get worried.

212
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:44,320
I will explain it to Aunt later.

213
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:46,760
Dear, I am worried

214
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:50,400
about what I will offer
for your wedding.

215
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:52,880
Uncle, why are you worried?

216
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:56,920
I told you. A nuptial chain
is enough for a bride.

217
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,240
And my groom will bring
my nuptial chain.

218
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:04,200
Uncle, am I so shameless

219
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:07,000
that I will sell your land
and wear ornaments?

220
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:14,880
Uncle, after mom left,
you have brought us up.

221
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:16,560
You brought us up.

222
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,600
You made us worthy.

223
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:24,040
You have given me
twice the love of a mother.

224
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,000
Oh no!

225
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,440
- Uncle, mom.
- Mom?

226
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:35,880
- Mom!
- What mom?

227
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:38,520
Oh! I forgot the sweets!

228
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:42,120
[happy music]

229
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,560
- Why are you running?
- Sweets!

230
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:45,880
Where have you been since morning?

231
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:47,760
Later. I want to go to the farm.

232
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:49,440
What are you doing?

233
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:52,200
Oh God! This girl

234
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:54,080
is so troublesome.

235
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,360
I don't know
what will happen to her.

236
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:59,560
Enough.
I don't have to go to Rajkot.

237
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:01,880
- Box?
- Sweets.

238
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:02,960
Sweets?

239
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:06,240
Hey, give me some money.

240
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,760
- Me?
- Give it to me.

241
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:09,520
Where are you going in such a hurry?

242
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:11,720
- I will tell you later. Hey!
- Sorry.

243
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,040
He is a strange man.

244
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,120
- Uncle.
- Yes.

245
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:19,320
Where did she go to feed sweets
to in such a hurry?

246
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:22,040
- The one whose birthday is today.
- Birthday?

247
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,360
Didn't you understand?

248
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:26,600
[dramatic music]

249
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:34,440
[dramatic music]

250
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,800
Who is calling?

251
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,440
Mr Naren Ratan Singh.

252
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:46,400
Tell me, Mr Naren. Greetings.

253
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:49,520
Mr Mehul. I have left from Upleta.

254
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:52,520
I am coming to see the girl today.

255
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:55,680
Today? You were supposed
to come tomorrow, Mr Naren.

256
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:59,160
Yes. The work in the factory
got over before time.

257
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:02,320
So, I thought of completing
this program as soon as possible.

258
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:05,360
You are great, Mr Naren.

259
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:07,120
No problem. Come here.

260
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:11,360
Hey! Sir.

261
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:15,320
The boy who was supposed to come
to see the girl is coming today.

262
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,480
- What?
- Yes.

263
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:19,120
Go inside and tell
your aunt. Come on. Quick.

264
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:22,160
- Aunt Mani.
- Yes.

265
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:24,840
The boy who was supposed to come
to see the girl is coming today.

266
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:25,760
What?

267
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:28,720
He is supposed to reach
Upleta in some time.

268
